LOCAL FIX: Add a check to ensure that both environment variables are set before dereferencing. Modify the is_admin function as follows:

static int is_admin(void) {
    const char *u = getenv("USER");
    const char *a = getenv("ADMIN_USER");
    if (u == NULL || a == NULL) {
        return 0; // Not admin if either variable is unset
    }
    return *u == *a;
}

GLOBAL FIX: Implement a more robust configuration management system that ensures all necessary environment variables are set before the application runs. This could involve using a configuration file or a setup script that validates and sets default values for environment variables, preventing null dereferences at runtime.
